5844#if PLATFORM(GTK) || PLATFORM(WPE)
5845
5846static Frame* targetFrameForEditing(WebPage& page)
5847{
5848 Frame& targetFrame = page.corePage()->focusController().focusedOrMainFrame();
5849
5850 Editor& editor = targetFrame.editor();
5851 if (!editor.canEdit())
5852 return nullptr;
5853
5854 if (editor.hasComposition()) {
5855 // We should verify the parent node of this IME composition node are
5856 // editable because JavaScript may delete a parent node of the composition
5857 // node. In this case, WebKit crashes while deleting texts from the parent
5858 // node, which doesn't exist any longer.
5859 if (auto range = editor.compositionRange()) {
5860 if (!range->startContainer().isContentEditable())
5861 return nullptr;
5862 }
5863 }
5864 return &targetFrame;
5865}
5866
5867void WebPage::cancelComposition(const String& compositionString)
5868{
5869 if (auto* targetFrame = targetFrameForEditing(*this))
5870 targetFrame->editor().confirmComposition(compositionString);
5871}
5872
5873void WebPage::deleteSurrounding(int64_t offset, unsigned characterCount)
5874{
5875 auto* targetFrame = targetFrameForEditing(*this);
5876 if (!targetFrame)
5877 return;
5878
5879 auto& selection = targetFrame->selection().selection();
5880 if (selection.isNone())
5881 return;
5882
5883 auto selectionStart = selection.visibleStart();
5884 auto surroundingRange = makeSimpleRange(startOfEditableContent(selectionStart), selectionStart);
5885 if (!surroundingRange)
5886 return;
5887
5888 auto& rootNode = surroundingRange->start.container->treeScope().rootNode();
5889 auto characterRange = WebCore::CharacterRange(WebCore::characterCount(*surroundingRange) + offset, characterCount);
5890 auto selectionRange = resolveCharacterRange(makeRangeSelectingNodeContents(rootNode), characterRange);
5891
5892 targetFrame->editor().setIgnoreSelectionChanges(true);
5893 targetFrame->selection().setSelection(VisibleSelection(selectionRange));
5894 targetFrame->editor().deleteSelectionWithSmartDelete(false);
5895 targetFrame->editor().setIgnoreSelectionChanges(false);
5896 sendEditorStateUpdate();
5897}
5898
5899#endif

5906void WebPage::didChangeContents()

5910
5911void WebPage::didChangeOverflowScrollPosition()
5912{
5913 didChangeSelectionOrOverflowScrollPosition();
5914}
5915
5916void WebPage::didChangeSelection()
5917{
5918 didChangeSelectionOrOverflowScrollPosition();
5919}
5920
5921void WebPage::didChangeSelectionOrOverflowScrollPosition()
5922{
5923 Frame& frame = m_page->focusController().focusedOrMainFrame();
5924 // The act of getting Dictionary Popup info can make selection changes that we should not propagate to the UIProcess.
5925 // Specifically, if there is a caret selection, it will change to a range selection of the word around the caret. And
5926 // then it will change back.
5927 if (frame.editor().isGettingDictionaryPopupInfo())
5928 return;
5929
5930 // Similarly, we don't want to propagate changes to the web process when inserting text asynchronously, since we will
5931 // end up with a range selection very briefly right before inserting the text.
5932 if (m_isSelectingTextWhileInsertingAsynchronously)
5933 return;
5934
5935#if PLATFORM(MAC)
5936 bool hasPreviouslyFocusedDueToUserInteraction = m_hasEverFocusedElementDueToUserInteractionSincePageTransition;
5937 m_hasEverFocusedElementDueToUserInteractionSincePageTransition |= m_userIsInteracting;
5938
5939 if (!hasPreviouslyFocusedDueToUserInteraction && m_hasEverFocusedElementDueToUserInteractionSincePageTransition) {
5940#if HAVE(TOUCH_BAR)
5941 if (frame.document()->quirks().isTouchBarUpdateSupressedForHiddenContentEditable()) {
5942 m_isTouchBarUpdateSupressedForHiddenContentEditable = true;
5943 send(Messages::WebPageProxy::SetIsTouchBarUpdateSupressedForHiddenContentEditable(m_isTouchBarUpdateSupressedForHiddenContentEditable));
5944 }
5945
5946 if (frame.document()->quirks().isNeverRichlyEditableForTouchBar()) {
5947 m_isNeverRichlyEditableForTouchBar = true;
5948 send(Messages::WebPageProxy::SetIsNeverRichlyEditableForTouchBar(m_isNeverRichlyEditableForTouchBar));
5949 }
5950#endif
5951
5952 send(Messages::WebPageProxy::SetHasHadSelectionChangesFromUserInteraction(m_hasEverFocusedElementDueToUserInteractionSincePageTransition));
5953 }
5954
5955 // Abandon the current inline input session if selection changed for any other reason but an input method direct action.
5956 // FIXME: This logic should be in WebCore.
5957 // FIXME: Many changes that affect composition node do not go through didChangeSelection(). We need to do something when DOM manipulation affects the composition, because otherwise input method's idea about it will be different from Editor's.
5958 // FIXME: We can't cancel composition when selection changes to NoSelection, but we probably should.
5959 if (frame.editor().hasComposition() && !frame.editor().ignoreSelectionChanges() && !frame.selection().isNone()) {
5960 frame.editor().cancelComposition();
5961 discardedComposition();
5962 return;
5963 }
5964#endif
5965
5966 scheduleFullEditorStateUpdate();
5967}
5968
5969void WebPage::resetFocusedElementForFrame(WebFrame* frame)
5970{
5971 if (!m_focusedElement)
5972 return;
5973
5974 if (frame->isMainFrame() || m_focusedElement->document().frame() == frame->coreFrame()) {
5975#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
5976 send(Messages::WebPageProxy::ElementDidBlur());
5977#elif PLATFORM(MAC)
5978 send(Messages::WebPageProxy::SetEditableElementIsFocused(false));
5979#endif
5980 m_focusedElement = nullptr;
5981 }
5982}
5983
5984void WebPage::elementDidRefocus(WebCore::Element& element)
5985{
5986 elementDidFocus(element);
5987
5988 if (m_userIsInteracting)
5989 scheduleFullEditorStateUpdate();
5990}
5991
5992bool WebPage::shouldDispatchUpdateAfterFocusingElement(const Element& element) const
5993{
5994 if (m_focusedElement == &element || m_recentlyBlurredElement == &element) {
5995#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
5996 return !m_isShowingInputViewForFocusedElement;
5997#else
5998 return false;
5999#endif
6000 }
6001 return true;
6002}
6003
6004static bool isTextFormControlOrEditableContent(const WebCore::Element& element)
6005{
6006 return is<HTMLTextFormControlElement>(element) || element.hasEditableStyle();
6007}
6008
6009void WebPage::elementDidFocus(WebCore::Element& element)
6010{
6011 if (!shouldDispatchUpdateAfterFocusingElement(element)) {
6012 updateInputContextAfterBlurringAndRefocusingElementIfNeeded(element);
6013 m_focusedElement = &element;
6014 m_recentlyBlurredElement = nullptr;
6015 return;
6016 }
6017
6018 if (is<HTMLSelectElement>(element) || isTextFormControlOrEditableContent(element)) {
6019 m_focusedElement = &element;
6020 m_hasPendingInputContextUpdateAfterBlurringAndRefocusingElement = false;
6021
6022#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
6023
6024#if ENABLE(FULLSCREEN_API)
6025 if (element.document().fullscreenManager().isFullscreen())
6026 element.document().fullscreenManager().cancelFullscreen();
6027#endif
6028
6029 ++m_currentFocusedElementIdentifier;
6030 auto information = focusedElementInformation();
6031 if (!information)
6032 return;
6033
6034 RefPtr<API::Object> userData;
6035
6036 m_formClient->willBeginInputSession(this, &element, WebFrame::fromCoreFrame(*element.document().frame()), m_userIsInteracting, userData);
6037
6038 send(Messages::WebPageProxy::ElementDidFocus(information.value(), m_userIsInteracting, m_recentlyBlurredElement, m_lastActivityStateChanges, UserData(WebProcess::singleton().transformObjectsToHandles(userData.get()).get())));
6039#elif PLATFORM(MAC)
6040 // FIXME: This can be unified with the iOS code above by bringing ElementDidFocus to macOS.
6041 // This also doesn't take other noneditable controls into account, such as input type color.
6042 send(Messages::WebPageProxy::SetEditableElementIsFocused(!element.hasTagName(WebCore::HTMLNames::selectTag)));
6043#endif
6044 m_recentlyBlurredElement = nullptr;
6045 }
6046}
6047
6048void WebPage::elementDidBlur(WebCore::Element& element)
6049{
6050 if (m_focusedElement == &element) {
6051 m_recentlyBlurredElement = WTFMove(m_focusedElement);
6052 callOnMainRunLoop([protectedThis = makeRefPtr(this)] {
6053 if (protectedThis->m_recentlyBlurredElement) {
6054#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
6055 protectedThis->send(Messages::WebPageProxy::ElementDidBlur());
6056#elif PLATFORM(MAC)
6057 protectedThis->send(Messages::WebPageProxy::SetEditableElementIsFocused(false));
6058#endif
6059 }
6060 protectedThis->m_recentlyBlurredElement = nullptr;
6061 });
6062 m_hasPendingInputContextUpdateAfterBlurringAndRefocusingElement = false;
6063 }
6064}
6065
6066void WebPage::focusedElementDidChangeInputMode(WebCore::Element& element, WebCore::InputMode mode)
6067{
6068 if (m_focusedElement != &element)
6069 return;
6070
6071#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
6072 ASSERT(is<HTMLElement>(element));
6073 ASSERT(downcast<HTMLElement>(element).canonicalInputMode() == mode);
6074
6075 if (!isTextFormControlOrEditableContent(element))
6076 return;
6077
6078 send(Messages::WebPageProxy::FocusedElementDidChangeInputMode(mode));
6079#else
6080 UNUSED_PARAM(mode);
6081#endif
6082}

6210 });

6213bool WebPage::canShowMIMEType(const String& mimeType) const
6214{
6215 return canShowMIMEType(mimeType, [&](auto& mimeType, auto allowedPlugins) {
6216 return m_page->pluginData().supportsWebVisibleMimeType(mimeType, allowedPlugins);
6217 });
6218}
6219
6220bool WebPage::canShowMIMEType(const String& mimeType, const Function<bool(const String&, PluginData::AllowedPluginTypes)>& pluginsSupport) const
6221{
6222 if (MIMETypeRegistry::canShowMIMEType(mimeType))
6223 return true;
6224
6225 if (!mimeType.isNull() && m_mimeTypesWithCustomContentProviders.contains(mimeType))
6226 return true;
6227
6228 if (corePage()->mainFrame().arePluginsEnabled() && pluginsSupport(mimeType, PluginData::AllPlugins))
6229 return true;
6230
6231 // We can use application plugins even if plugins aren't enabled.
6232 if (pluginsSupport(mimeType, PluginData::OnlyApplicationPlugins))
6233 return true;
6234
6235 return false;
6236}

6238void WebPage::addTextCheckingRequest(uint64_t requestID, Ref<TextCheckingRequest>&& request)

6243void WebPage::didFinishCheckingText(uint64_t requestID, const Vector<TextCheckingResult>& result)
6244{
6245 RefPtr<TextCheckingRequest> request = m_pendingTextCheckingRequestMap.take(requestID);
6246 if (!request)
6247 return;
6248
6249 request->didSucceed(result);
6250}
6251
6252void WebPage::didCancelCheckingText(uint64_t requestID)
6253{
6254 RefPtr<TextCheckingRequest> request = m_pendingTextCheckingRequestMap.take(requestID);
6255 if (!request)
6256 return;
6257
6258 request->didCancel();
6259}

6275 return;

6279 m_drawingArea->setExposedContentRect(m_previousExposedContentRect);
6280#endif
6281}
6282
6283void WebPage::didCommitLoad(WebFrame* frame)
6284{
6285#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
6286 auto firstTransactionIDAfterDidCommitLoad = downcast<RemoteLayerTreeDrawingArea>(*m_drawingArea).nextTransactionID();
6287 frame->setFirstLayerTreeTransactionIDAfterDidCommitLoad(firstTransactionIDAfterDidCommitLoad);
6288 cancelPotentialTapInFrame(*frame);
6289#endif
6290 resetFocusedElementForFrame(frame);
6291
6292 if (!frame->isMainFrame())
6293 return;
6294
6295 if (m_drawingArea)
6296 m_drawingArea->sendEnterAcceleratedCompositingModeIfNeeded();
6297
6298 ASSERT(!frame->coreFrame()->loader().stateMachine().creatingInitialEmptyDocument());
6299 unfreezeLayerTree(LayerTreeFreezeReason::ProcessSwap);
6300
6301#if ENABLE(IMAGE_ANALYSIS)
6302 for (auto& [element, completionHandlers] : m_elementsPendingTextRecognition) {
6303 for (auto& completionHandler : completionHandlers)
6304 completionHandler({ });
6305 }
6306 m_elementsPendingTextRecognition.clear();
6307#endif
6308
6309#if ENABLE(RESOURCE_LOAD_STATISTICS)
6310 clearLoadedSubresourceDomains();
6311#endif
6312
6313 // If previous URL is invalid, then it's not a real page that's being navigated away from.
6314 // Most likely, this is actually the first load to be committed in this page.
6315 if (frame->coreFrame()->loader().previousURL().isValid())
6316 reportUsedFeatures();
6317
6318 // Only restore the scale factor for standard frame loads (of the main frame).
6319 if (frame->coreFrame()->loader().loadType() == FrameLoadType::Standard) {
6320 Page* page = frame->coreFrame()->page();
6321
6322#if PLATFORM(MAC)
6323 // As a very special case, we disable non-default layout modes in WKView for main-frame PluginDocuments.
6324 // Ideally we would only worry about this in WKView or the WKViewLayoutStrategies, but if we allow
6325 // a round-trip to the UI process, you'll see the wrong scale temporarily. So, we reset it here, and then
6326 // again later from the UI process.
6327 if (frame->coreFrame()->document()->isPluginDocument()) {
6328 scaleView(1);
6329 setUseFixedLayout(false);
6330 }
6331#endif
6332
6333 if (page && page->pageScaleFactor() != 1)
6334 scalePage(1, IntPoint());
6335 }
6336
6337 m_didUpdateRenderingAfterCommittingLoad = false;
6338
6339#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
6340 m_hasReceivedVisibleContentRectsAfterDidCommitLoad = false;
6341 m_hasRestoredExposedContentRectAfterDidCommitLoad = false;
6342 m_lastTransactionIDWithScaleChange = firstTransactionIDAfterDidCommitLoad;
6343 m_scaleWasSetByUIProcess = false;
6344 m_userHasChangedPageScaleFactor = false;
6345 m_estimatedLatency = Seconds(1.0 / 60);
6346 m_shouldRevealCurrentSelectionAfterInsertion = true;
6347 m_lastLayerTreeTransactionIdAndPageScaleBeforeScalingPage = std::nullopt;
6348
6349#if ENABLE(IOS_TOUCH_EVENTS)
6350 EventDispatcher::TouchEventQueue queuedEvents;
6351 WebProcess::singleton().eventDispatcher().takeQueuedTouchEventsForPage(*this, queuedEvents);
6352 cancelAsynchronousTouchEvents(WTFMove(queuedEvents));
6353#endif
6354#endif // PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
6355
6356#if ENABLE(META_VIEWPORT)
6357 resetViewportDefaultConfiguration(frame);
6358 const Frame* coreFrame = frame->coreFrame();
6359
6360 bool viewportChanged = false;
6361
6362 LOG_WITH_STREAM(VisibleRects, stream << "WebPage " << m_identifier.toUInt64() << " didCommitLoad setting content size to " << coreFrame->view()->contentsSize());
6363 if (m_viewportConfiguration.setContentsSize(coreFrame->view()->contentsSize()))
6364 viewportChanged = true;
6365
6366 if (m_viewportConfiguration.setViewportArguments(coreFrame->document()->viewportArguments()))
6367 viewportChanged = true;
6368
6369 if (m_viewportConfiguration.setIsKnownToLayOutWiderThanViewport(false))
6370 viewportChanged = true;
6371
6372 if (viewportChanged)
6373 viewportConfigurationChanged();
6374#endif // ENABLE(META_VIEWPORT)
6375
6376#if ENABLE(TEXT_AUTOSIZING)
6377 m_textAutoSizingAdjustmentTimer.stop();
6378#endif
6379
6380#if USE(OS_STATE)
6381 m_loadCommitTime = WallTime::now();
6382#endif
6383
6384 themeColorChanged();
6385
6386 WebProcess::singleton().updateActivePages(m_processDisplayName);
6387
6388 updateMainFrameScrollOffsetPinning();
6389
6390 updateMockAccessibilityElementAfterCommittingLoad();
6391}
6392
6393void WebPage::didFinishDocumentLoad(WebFrame& frame)
6394{
6395 if (!frame.isMainFrame())
6396 return;
6397
6398#if ENABLE(VIEWPORT_RESIZING)
6399 shrinkToFitContent(ZoomToInitialScale::Yes);
6400#endif
6401}
6402
6403void WebPage::didFinishLoad(WebFrame& frame)
6404{
6405 if (!frame.isMainFrame())
6406 return;
6407
6408 WebProcess::singleton().sendPrewarmInformation(frame.url());
6409
6410#if ENABLE(VIEWPORT_RESIZING)
6411 shrinkToFitContent(ZoomToInitialScale::Yes);
6412#endif
6413}

6471
6472void WebPage::sendEditorStateUpdate()
6473{
6474 Frame& frame = m_page->focusController().focusedOrMainFrame();
6475 if (frame.editor().ignoreSelectionChanges())
6476 return;
6477
6478 m_hasPendingEditorStateUpdate = false;
6479
6480 // If we immediately dispatch an EditorState update to the UI process, layout may not be up to date yet.
6481 // If that is the case, just send what we have (i.e. don't include post-layout data) and wait until the
6482 // next layer tree commit to compute and send the complete EditorState over.
6483 auto state = editorState();
6484 send(Messages::WebPageProxy::EditorStateChanged(state));
6485
6486 if (state.isMissingPostLayoutData)
6487 scheduleFullEditorStateUpdate();
6488}
6489
6490void WebPage::scheduleFullEditorStateUpdate()
6491{
6492 if (m_hasPendingEditorStateUpdate)
6493 return;
6494
6495 m_hasPendingEditorStateUpdate = true;
6496 // FIXME: Scheduling a compositing layer flush here can be more expensive than necessary.
6497 // Instead, we should just compute and send post-layout editor state during the next frame.
6498 m_drawingArea->triggerRenderingUpdate();
6499}

6589
6590unsigned WebPage::extendIncrementalRenderingSuppression()
6591{
6592 unsigned token = m_maximumRenderingSuppressionToken + 1;
6593 while (!HashSet<unsigned>::isValidValue(token) || m_activeRenderingSuppressionTokens.contains(token))
6594 token++;
6595
6596 m_activeRenderingSuppressionTokens.add(token);
6597 m_page->mainFrame().view()->setVisualUpdatesAllowedByClient(false);
6598
6599 m_maximumRenderingSuppressionToken = token;
6600
6601 return token;
6602}
6603
6604void WebPage::stopExtendingIncrementalRenderingSuppression(unsigned token)
6605{
6606 if (!m_activeRenderingSuppressionTokens.remove(token))
6607 return;
6608
6609 m_page->mainFrame().view()->setVisualUpdatesAllowedByClient(!shouldExtendIncrementalRenderingSuppression());
6610}

6627Ref<DocumentLoader> WebPage::createDocumentLoader(Frame& frame, const ResourceRequest& request, const SubstituteData& substituteData)
6628{
6629 Ref<WebDocumentLoader> documentLoader = WebDocumentLoader::create(request, substituteData);
6630
6631 documentLoader->setLastNavigationWasAppBound(m_lastNavigationWasAppBound);
6632
6633 if (frame.isMainFrame()) {
6634 if (m_pendingNavigationID) {
6635 documentLoader->setNavigationID(m_pendingNavigationID);
6636 m_pendingNavigationID = 0;
6637 }
6638
6639 if (m_pendingWebsitePolicies) {
6640 m_allowsContentJavaScriptFromMostRecentNavigation = m_pendingWebsitePolicies->allowsContentJavaScript;
6641 WebsitePoliciesData::applyToDocumentLoader(WTFMove(*m_pendingWebsitePolicies), documentLoader);
6642 m_pendingWebsitePolicies = std::nullopt;
6643 }
6644 }
6645
6646 return documentLoader;
6647}

6649void WebPage::updateCachedDocumentLoader(WebDocumentLoader& documentLoader, Frame& frame)
6650{
6651 if (m_pendingNavigationID && frame.isMainFrame()) {
6652 documentLoader.setNavigationID(m_pendingNavigationID);
6653 m_pendingNavigationID = 0;
6654 }
6655}

6756
6757void WebPage::updateIntrinsicContentSizeIfNeeded(const WebCore::IntSize& size)
6758{
6759 m_pendingIntrinsicContentSize = std::nullopt;
6760 if (!minimumSizeForAutoLayout().width() && !sizeToContentAutoSizeMaximumSize().width() && !sizeToContentAutoSizeMaximumSize().height())
6761 return;
6762 ASSERT(mainFrameView());
6763 ASSERT(mainFrameView()->isFixedWidthAutoSizeEnabled() || mainFrameView()->isSizeToContentAutoSizeEnabled());
6764 ASSERT(!mainFrameView()->needsLayout());
6765 if (m_lastSentIntrinsicContentSize == size)
6766 return;
6767 m_lastSentIntrinsicContentSize = size;
6768 send(Messages::WebPageProxy::DidChangeIntrinsicContentSize(size));
6769}

6772{

6774 updateIntrinsicContentSizeIfNeeded(*pendingSize);
6775}

6777void WebPage::scheduleIntrinsicContentSizeUpdate(const IntSize& size)
6778{
6779 if (!minimumSizeForAutoLayout().width() && !sizeToContentAutoSizeMaximumSize().width() && !sizeToContentAutoSizeMaximumSize().height())
6780 return;
6781 ASSERT(mainFrameView());
6782 ASSERT(mainFrameView()->isFixedWidthAutoSizeEnabled() || mainFrameView()->isSizeToContentAutoSizeEnabled());
6783 ASSERT(!mainFrameView()->needsLayout());
6784 m_pendingIntrinsicContentSize = size;
6785}
6786
6787void WebPage::dispatchDidReachLayoutMilestone(OptionSet<WebCore::LayoutMilestone> milestones)
6788{
6789 RefPtr<API::Object> userData;
6790 injectedBundleLoaderClient().didReachLayoutMilestone(*this, milestones, userData);
6791
6792 // Clients should not set userData for this message, and it won't be passed through.
6793 ASSERT(!userData);
6794
6795 // The drawing area might want to defer dispatch of didLayout to the UI process.
6796 if (m_drawingArea) {
6797 static auto paintMilestones = OptionSet<WebCore::LayoutMilestone> { DidHitRelevantRepaintedObjectsAreaThreshold, DidFirstFlushForHeaderLayer, DidFirstPaintAfterSuppressedIncrementalRendering, DidRenderSignificantAmountOfText, DidFirstMeaningfulPaint };
6798 auto drawingAreaRelatedMilestones = milestones & paintMilestones;
6799 if (drawingAreaRelatedMilestones && m_drawingArea->addMilestonesToDispatch(drawingAreaRelatedMilestones))
6800 milestones.remove(drawingAreaRelatedMilestones);
6801 }
6802 if (milestones.contains(DidFirstLayout) && mainFrameView()) {
6803 // Ensure we never send DidFirstLayout milestone without updating the intrinsic size.
6804 updateIntrinsicContentSizeIfNeeded(mainFrameView()->autoSizingIntrinsicContentSize());
6805 }
6806
6807 send(Messages::WebPageProxy::DidReachLayoutMilestone(milestones));
6808}

6867
6868void WebPage::stopAllURLSchemeTasks()
6869{
6870 HashSet<WebURLSchemeHandlerProxy*> handlers;
6871 for (auto& handler : m_schemeToURLSchemeHandlerProxyMap.values())
6872 handlers.add(handler.get());
6873
6874 for (auto* handler : handlers)
6875 handler->stopAllTasks();
6876}
6877
6878void WebPage::registerURLSchemeHandler(uint64_t handlerIdentifier, const String& scheme)
6879{
6880 WEBPAGE_RELEASE_LOG(Process, "registerURLSchemeHandler: Registered handler %" PRIu64 " for the '%s' scheme", handlerIdentifier, scheme.utf8().data());
6881 WebCore::LegacySchemeRegistry::registerURLSchemeAsHandledBySchemeHandler(scheme);
6882 WebCore::LegacySchemeRegistry::registerURLSchemeAsCORSEnabled(scheme);
6883 auto schemeResult = m_schemeToURLSchemeHandlerProxyMap.add(scheme, WebURLSchemeHandlerProxy::create(*this, handlerIdentifier));
6884 m_identifierToURLSchemeHandlerProxyMap.add(handlerIdentifier, schemeResult.iterator->value.get());
6885}
6886
6887void WebPage::urlSchemeTaskWillPerformRedirection(uint64_t handlerIdentifier, uint64_t taskIdentifier, ResourceResponse&& response, ResourceRequest&& request, CompletionHandler<void(WebCore::ResourceRequest&&)>&& completionHandler)
6888{
6889 auto* handler = m_identifierToURLSchemeHandlerProxyMap.get(handlerIdentifier);
6890 ASSERT(handler);
6891
6892 auto actualNewRequest = request;
6893 handler->taskDidPerformRedirection(taskIdentifier, WTFMove(response), WTFMove(request), WTFMove(completionHandler));
6894}
6895
6896void WebPage::urlSchemeTaskDidPerformRedirection(uint64_t handlerIdentifier, uint64_t taskIdentifier, ResourceResponse&& response, ResourceRequest&& request)
6897{
6898 auto* handler = m_identifierToURLSchemeHandlerProxyMap.get(handlerIdentifier);
6899 ASSERT(handler);
6900
6901 handler->taskDidPerformRedirection(taskIdentifier, WTFMove(response), WTFMove(request), [] (ResourceRequest&&) {});
6902}
6903
6904void WebPage::urlSchemeTaskDidReceiveResponse(uint64_t handlerIdentifier, uint64_t taskIdentifier, const ResourceResponse& response)
6905{
6906 auto* handler = m_identifierToURLSchemeHandlerProxyMap.get(handlerIdentifier);
6907 ASSERT(handler);
6908
6909 handler->taskDidReceiveResponse(taskIdentifier, response);
6910}
6911
6912void WebPage::urlSchemeTaskDidReceiveData(uint64_t handlerIdentifier, uint64_t taskIdentifier, const IPC::DataReference& data)
6913{
6914 auto* handler = m_identifierToURLSchemeHandlerProxyMap.get(handlerIdentifier);
6915 ASSERT(handler);
6916
6917 handler->taskDidReceiveData(taskIdentifier, data.size(), data.data());
6918}
6919
6920void WebPage::urlSchemeTaskDidComplete(uint64_t handlerIdentifier, uint64_t taskIdentifier, const ResourceError& error)
6921{
6922 auto* handler = m_identifierToURLSchemeHandlerProxyMap.get(handlerIdentifier);
6923 ASSERT(handler);
6924
6925 handler->taskDidComplete(taskIdentifier, error);
6926}
6927
6928void WebPage::setIsSuspended(bool suspended)
6929{
6930 if (m_isSuspended == suspended)
6931 return;
6932
6933 m_isSuspended = suspended;
6934
6935 if (!suspended)
6936 return;
6937
6938 // Unfrozen on drawing area reset.
6939 freezeLayerTree(LayerTreeFreezeReason::PageSuspended);
6940
6941 // Only the committed WebPage gets application visibility notifications from the UIProcess, so make sure
6942 // we don't hold a BackgroundApplication freeze reason when transitioning from committed to suspended.
6943 unfreezeLayerTree(LayerTreeFreezeReason::BackgroundApplication);
6944
6945 WebProcess::singleton().sendPrewarmInformation(mainWebFrame().url());
6946
6947 suspendForProcessSwap();
6948}
6949
6950void WebPage::frameBecameRemote(FrameIdentifier frameID, GlobalFrameIdentifier&& remoteFrameIdentifier, GlobalWindowIdentifier&& remoteWindowIdentifier)
6951{
6952 RefPtr<WebFrame> frame = WebProcess::singleton().webFrame(frameID);
6953 if (!frame)
6954 return;
6955
6956 if (frame->page() != this)
6957 return;
6958
6959 auto* coreFrame = frame->coreFrame();
6960 auto* previousWindow = coreFrame->window();
6961 if (!previousWindow)
6962 return;
6963
6964 auto remoteFrame = RemoteFrame::create(WTFMove(remoteFrameIdentifier));
6965 auto remoteWindow = RemoteDOMWindow::create(remoteFrame.copyRef(), WTFMove(remoteWindowIdentifier));
6966
6967 remoteFrame->setOpener(frame->coreFrame()->loader().opener());
6968
6969 auto jsWindowProxies = frame->coreFrame()->windowProxy().releaseJSWindowProxies();
6970 remoteFrame->windowProxy().setJSWindowProxies(WTFMove(jsWindowProxies));
6971 remoteFrame->windowProxy().setDOMWindow(remoteWindow.ptr());
6972
6973 coreFrame->setView(nullptr);
6974 coreFrame->willDetachPage();
6975 coreFrame->detachFromPage();
6976
6977 if (frame->isMainFrame())
6978 close();
6979}

6981#if ENABLE(RESOURCE_LOAD_STATISTICS)
6982void WebPage::hasStorageAccess(RegistrableDomain&& subFrameDomain, RegistrableDomain&& topFrameDomain, WebFrame& frame, CompletionHandler<void(bool)>&& completionHandler)
6983{
6984 if (hasPageLevelStorageAccess(topFrameDomain, subFrameDomain)) {
6985 completionHandler(true);
6986 return;
6987 }
6988
6989 WebProcess::singleton().ensureNetworkProcessConnection().connection().sendWithAsyncReply(Messages::NetworkConnectionToWebProcess::HasStorageAccess(WTFMove(subFrameDomain), WTFMove(topFrameDomain), frame.frameID(), m_identifier), WTFMove(completionHandler));
6990}
6991
6992void WebPage::requestStorageAccess(RegistrableDomain&& subFrameDomain, RegistrableDomain&& topFrameDomain, WebFrame& frame, StorageAccessScope scope, CompletionHandler<void(WebCore::RequestStorageAccessResult)>&& completionHandler)
6993{
6994 WebProcess::singleton().ensureNetworkProcessConnection().connection().sendWithAsyncReply(Messages::NetworkConnectionToWebProcess::RequestStorageAccess(WTFMove(subFrameDomain), WTFMove(topFrameDomain), frame.frameID(), m_identifier, m_webPageProxyIdentifier, scope), [this, protectedThis = makeRef(*this), completionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler), frame = makeRef(frame), pageID = m_identifier, frameID = frame.frameID()](RequestStorageAccessResult result) mutable {
6995 if (result.wasGranted == StorageAccessWasGranted::Yes) {
6996 switch (result.scope) {
6997 case StorageAccessScope::PerFrame:
6998 frame->frameLoaderClient()->setHasFrameSpecificStorageAccess({ frameID, pageID });
6999 break;
7000 case StorageAccessScope::PerPage:
7001 addDomainWithPageLevelStorageAccess(result.topFrameDomain, result.subFrameDomain);
7002 break;
7003 }
7004 }
7005 completionHandler(result);
7006 });
7007}
7008
7009void WebPage::addDomainWithPageLevelStorageAccess(const RegistrableDomain& topLevelDomain, const RegistrableDomain& resourceDomain)
7010{
7011 m_domainsWithPageLevelStorageAccess.add(topLevelDomain, resourceDomain);
7012
7013 // Some sites have quirks where multiple login domains require storage access.
7014 if (auto additionalLoginDomain = NetworkStorageSession::findAdditionalLoginDomain(topLevelDomain, resourceDomain))
7015 m_domainsWithPageLevelStorageAccess.add(topLevelDomain, *additionalLoginDomain);
7016}
7017
7018bool WebPage::hasPageLevelStorageAccess(const RegistrableDomain& topLevelDomain, const RegistrableDomain& resourceDomain) const
7019{
7020 auto it = m_domainsWithPageLevelStorageAccess.find(topLevelDomain);
7021 return it != m_domainsWithPageLevelStorageAccess.end() && it->value == resourceDomain;
7022}
7023
7024void WebPage::clearPageLevelStorageAccess()
7025{
7026 m_domainsWithPageLevelStorageAccess.clear();
7027}

7073WebCore::DOMPasteAccessResponse WebPage::requestDOMPasteAccess(const String& originIdentifier)
7074{
7075 auto response = WebCore::DOMPasteAccessResponse::DeniedForGesture;
7076#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
7077 // FIXME: Computing and sending an autocorrection context is a workaround for the fact that autocorrection context
7078 // requests on iOS are currently synchronous in the web process. This allows us to immediately fulfill pending
7079 // autocorrection context requests in the UI process on iOS before handling the DOM paste request. This workaround
7080 // should be removed once <rdar://problem/16207002> is resolved.
7081 send(Messages::WebPageProxy::HandleAutocorrectionContext(autocorrectionContext()));
7082#endif
7083 sendSyncWithDelayedReply(Messages::WebPageProxy::RequestDOMPasteAccess(rectForElementAtInteractionLocation(), originIdentifier), Messages::WebPageProxy::RequestDOMPasteAccess::Reply(response));
7084 return response;
7085}

7218
7219RefPtr<Element> WebPage::elementForContext(const ElementContext& elementContext) const
7220{
7221 if (elementContext.webPageIdentifier != m_identifier)
7222 return nullptr;
7223
7224 auto* document = Document::allDocumentsMap().get(elementContext.documentIdentifier);
7225 if (!document)
7226 return nullptr;
7227
7228 if (document->page() != m_page.get())
7229 return nullptr;
7230
7231 return document->searchForElementByIdentifier(elementContext.elementIdentifier);
7232}
7233
7234std::optional<WebCore::ElementContext> WebPage::contextForElement(WebCore::Element& element) const
7235{
7236 auto& document = element.document();
7237 if (!m_page || document.page() != m_page.get())
7238 return std::nullopt;
7239
7240 auto frame = document.frame();
7241 if (!frame)
7242 return std::nullopt;
7243
7244 return WebCore::ElementContext { element.clientRect(), m_identifier, document.identifier(), document.identifierForElement(element) };
7245}
7246
7247void WebPage::startTextManipulations(Vector<WebCore::TextManipulationController::ExclusionRule>&& exclusionRules, CompletionHandler<void()>&& completionHandler)
7248{
7249 if (!m_page)
7250 return;
7251
7252 auto mainDocument = makeRefPtr(m_page->mainFrame().document());
7253 if (!mainDocument)
7254 return;
7255
7256 mainDocument->textManipulationController().startObservingParagraphs([webPage = makeWeakPtr(*this)] (Document& document, const Vector<WebCore::TextManipulationController::ManipulationItem>& items) {
7257 auto* frame = document.frame();
7258 if (!webPage || !frame || webPage->mainFrame() != frame)
7259 return;
7260
7261 auto* webFrame = WebFrame::fromCoreFrame(*frame);
7262 if (!webFrame)
7263 return;
7264
7265 webPage->send(Messages::WebPageProxy::DidFindTextManipulationItems(items));
7266 }, WTFMove(exclusionRules));
7267 // For now, we assume startObservingParagraphs find all paragraphs synchronously at once.
7268 completionHandler();
7269}
7270
7271void completeTextManipulation(const Vector<WebCore::TextManipulationController::ManipulationItem>,
7272 CompletionHandler<void(const HashSet<WebCore::TextManipulationController::ItemIdentifier, WebCore::TextManipulationController::ManipulationFailure>&)>&&);
7273
7274void WebPage::completeTextManipulation(const Vector<WebCore::TextManipulationController::ManipulationItem>& items,
7275 CompletionHandler<void(bool allFailed, const Vector<WebCore::TextManipulationController::ManipulationFailure>&)>&& completionHandler)
7276{
7277 if (!m_page) {
7278 completionHandler(true, { });
7279 return;
7280 }
7281
7282 auto mainDocument = makeRefPtr(m_page->mainFrame().document());
7283 if (!mainDocument) {
7284 completionHandler(true, { });
7285 return;
7286 }
7287
7288 auto* controller = mainDocument->textManipulationControllerIfExists();
7289 if (!controller) {
7290 completionHandler(true, { });
7291 return;
7292 }
7293
7294 completionHandler(false, controller->completeManipulation(items));
7295}

7401
7402#if ENABLE(IMAGE_ANALYSIS)
7403
7404void WebPage::requestTextRecognition(WebCore::Element& element, CompletionHandler<void(RefPtr<WebCore::Element>&&)>&& completion)
7405{
7406 if (!is<HTMLElement>(element)) {
7407 if (completion)
7408 completion({ });
7409 return;
7410 }
7411
7412 auto htmlElement = makeRef(downcast<HTMLElement>(element));
7413 if (corePage()->hasCachedTextRecognitionResult(htmlElement.get())) {
7414 if (completion) {
7415 RefPtr<Element> imageOverlayHost;
7416 if (htmlElement->hasImageOverlay())
7417 imageOverlayHost = makeRefPtr(element);
7418 completion(WTFMove(imageOverlayHost));
7419 }
7420 return;
7421 }
7422
7423 auto matchIndex = m_elementsPendingTextRecognition.findMatching([&] (auto& elementAndCompletionHandlers) {
7424 return elementAndCompletionHandlers.first == &element;
7425 });
7426
7427 if (matchIndex != notFound) {
7428 if (completion)
7429 m_elementsPendingTextRecognition[matchIndex].second.append(WTFMove(completion));
7430 return;
7431 }
7432
7433 auto* renderer = element.renderer();
7434 if (!is<RenderImage>(renderer)) {
7435 if (completion)
7436 completion({ });
7437 return;
7438 }
7439
7440 auto& renderImage = downcast<RenderImage>(*renderer);
7441 auto bitmap = createShareableBitmap(renderImage, std::nullopt, AllowAnimatedImages::No);
7442 if (!bitmap) {
7443 if (completion)
7444 completion({ });
7445 return;
7446 }
7447
7448 ShareableBitmap::Handle bitmapHandle;
7449 bitmap->createHandle(bitmapHandle);
7450 if (bitmapHandle.isNull()) {
7451 if (completion)
7452 completion({ });
7453 return;
7454 }
7455
7456 Vector<CompletionHandler<void(RefPtr<Element>&&)>> completionHandlers;
7457 if (completion)
7458 completionHandlers.append(WTFMove(completion));
7459 m_elementsPendingTextRecognition.append({ makeWeakPtr(element), WTFMove(completionHandlers) });
7460
7461 auto imageURL = element.document().completeURL(renderImage.cachedImage()->url().string());
7462 sendWithAsyncReply(Messages::WebPageProxy::RequestTextRecognition(WTFMove(imageURL), WTFMove(bitmapHandle)), [webPage = makeWeakPtr(*this), weakElement = makeWeakPtr(element)] (auto&& result) {
7463 auto protectedPage = makeRefPtr(webPage.get());
7464 if (!protectedPage)
7465 return;
7466
7467 protectedPage->m_elementsPendingTextRecognition.removeAllMatching([&] (auto& elementAndCompletionHandlers) {
7468 auto& [element, completionHandlers] = elementAndCompletionHandlers;
7469 if (element)
7470 return false;
7471
7472 for (auto& completionHandler : completionHandlers)
7473 completionHandler({ });
7474 return true;
7475 });
7476
7477 auto protectedElement = makeRefPtr(weakElement.get());
7478 if (!protectedElement)
7479 return;
7480
7481 auto& htmlElement = downcast<HTMLElement>(*protectedElement);
7482 htmlElement.updateWithTextRecognitionResult(result);
7483
7484 auto matchIndex = protectedPage->m_elementsPendingTextRecognition.findMatching([&] (auto& elementAndCompletionHandlers) {
7485 return elementAndCompletionHandlers.first == &htmlElement;
7486 });
7487
7488 if (matchIndex == notFound)
7489 return;
7490
7491 auto imageOverlayHost = htmlElement.hasImageOverlay() ? makeRefPtr(htmlElement) : nullptr;
7492 for (auto& completionHandler : protectedPage->m_elementsPendingTextRecognition[matchIndex].second)
7493 completionHandler(imageOverlayHost.copyRef());
7494
7495 protectedPage->m_elementsPendingTextRecognition.remove(matchIndex);
7496 });
7497}
7498
7499void WebPage::updateWithTextRecognitionResult(const TextRecognitionResult& result, const ElementContext& context, const FloatPoint& location, CompletionHandler<void(TextRecognitionUpdateResult)>&& completionHandler)
7500{
7501 auto elementToUpdate = elementForContext(context);
7502 if (!is<HTMLElement>(elementToUpdate)) {
7503 completionHandler(TextRecognitionUpdateResult::NoText);
7504 return;
7505 }
7506
7507 downcast<HTMLElement>(*elementToUpdate).updateWithTextRecognitionResult(result);
7508 auto hitTestResult = corePage()->mainFrame().eventHandler().hitTestResultAtPoint(roundedIntPoint(location), {
7509 HitTestRequest::Type::ReadOnly,
7510 HitTestRequest::Type::Active,
7511 HitTestRequest::Type::AllowVisibleChildFrameContentOnly,
7512 });
7513
7514 auto nodeAtLocation = makeRefPtr(hitTestResult.innerNonSharedNode());
7515 auto updateResult = ([&] {
7516 if (!nodeAtLocation || nodeAtLocation->shadowHost() != elementToUpdate || !HTMLElement::isInsideImageOverlay(*nodeAtLocation))
7517 return TextRecognitionUpdateResult::NoText;
7518
7519#if ENABLE(DATA_DETECTION)
7520 if (findDataDetectionResultElementInImageOverlay(location, downcast<HTMLElement>(*elementToUpdate)))
7521 return TextRecognitionUpdateResult::DataDetector;
7522#endif
7523
7524 if (HTMLElement::isImageOverlayText(*nodeAtLocation))
7525 return TextRecognitionUpdateResult::Text;
7526
7527 return TextRecognitionUpdateResult::NoText;
7528 })();
7529
7530 completionHandler(updateResult);
7531}
7532
7533#endif // ENABLE(IMAGE_ANALYSIS)
7534

7573
7574Vector<RefPtr<SandboxExtension>> WebPage::consumeSandboxExtensions(SandboxExtension::HandleArray&& sandboxExtensions)
7575{
7576 Vector<RefPtr<SandboxExtension>> dragSandboxExtensions;
7577 for (auto& sandboxExtension : sandboxExtensions) {
7578 auto extension = SandboxExtension::create(WTFMove(sandboxExtension));
7579 if (!extension)
7580 continue;
7581 bool ok = extension->consume();
7582 ASSERT_UNUSED(ok, ok);
7583 dragSandboxExtensions.append(WTFMove(extension));
7584 }
7585 return dragSandboxExtensions;
7586}
7587
7588void WebPage::revokeSandboxExtensions(Vector<RefPtr<SandboxExtension>>& sandboxExtensions)
7589{
7590 for (auto& sandboxExtension : sandboxExtensions)
7591 sandboxExtension->revoke();
7592 sandboxExtensions.clear();
7593}
7594
7595#if ENABLE(APP_HIGHLIGHTS)
7596bool WebPage::createAppHighlightInSelectedRange(WebCore::CreateNewGroupForHighlight createNewGroup, WebCore::HighlightRequestOriginatedInApp requestOriginatedInApp)
7597{
7598 SetForScope<WebCore::CreateNewGroupForHighlight> highlightIsNewGroupScope { m_highlightIsNewGroup, createNewGroup };
7599 SetForScope<WebCore::HighlightRequestOriginatedInApp> highlightRequestOriginScope { m_highlightRequestOriginatedInApp, requestOriginatedInApp };
7600
7601 auto document = makeRefPtr(m_page->focusController().focusedOrMainFrame().document());
7602
7603 auto frame = makeRefPtr(document->frame());
7604 if (!frame)
7605 return false;
7606
7607 auto selectionRange = frame->selection().selection().toNormalizedRange();
7608 if (!selectionRange)
7609 return false;
7610
7611 document->appHighlightRegister().addAppHighlight(StaticRange::create(selectionRange.value()));
7612 document->appHighlightStorage().storeAppHighlight(StaticRange::create(selectionRange.value()));
7613
7614 return true;
7615}
7616
7617void WebPage::restoreAppHighlightsAndScrollToIndex(const Vector<SharedMemory::IPCHandle>&& memoryHandles, const std::optional<unsigned> index)
7618{
7619 auto document = makeRefPtr(m_page->focusController().focusedOrMainFrame().document());
7620
7621 unsigned i = 0;
7622 for (const auto& ipcHandle : memoryHandles) {
7623 auto sharedMemory = SharedMemory::map(ipcHandle.handle, SharedMemory::Protection::ReadOnly);
7624 if (!sharedMemory)
7625 continue;
7626
7627 document->appHighlightStorage().restoreAndScrollToAppHighlight(SharedBuffer::create(static_cast<const uint8_t*>(sharedMemory->data()), ipcHandle.dataSize), i == index ? ScrollToHighlight::Yes : ScrollToHighlight::No);
7628 i++;
7629 }
7630}
7631
7632void WebPage::setAppHighlightsVisibility(WebCore::HighlightVisibility appHighlightVisibility)
7633{
7634 m_appHighlightsVisible = appHighlightVisibility;
7635 for (RefPtr<Frame> frame = m_mainFrame->coreFrame(); frame; frame = frame->tree().traverseNextRendered()) {
7636 if (auto document = makeRefPtr(frame->document()))
7637 document->appHighlightRegister().setHighlightVisibility(appHighlightVisibility);
7638 }
7639}

7643#if ENABLE(MEDIA_SESSION_COORDINATOR)
7644void WebPage::createMediaSessionCoordinator(const String& identifier, CompletionHandler<void(bool)>&& completionHandler)
7645{
7646 auto* document = m_mainFrame->coreFrame()->document();
7647 if (!document || !document->domWindow()) {
7648 completionHandler(false);
7649 return;
7650 }
7651
7652 m_page->setMediaSessionCoordinator(RemoteMediaSessionCoordinator::create(*this, identifier));
7653 completionHandler(true);
7654}
